1function H = messmatrix_new(P, r, delta, ind, lambda)
 2
 3num_points = numel(r);
 4% d ist delta, bei regelmäßigen Abständen
 5d = delta;
 6
 7%Ableitungen nach phi0
 8d_phi0 = zeros(num_points, 2);
 9for p=2:num_points
10%     d = distance(P(p-1, 1),P(p-1, 2),P(p, 1),P(p, 2));
11    d_phi0(p, 1) = d_phi0(p-1, 1) - d*sin(P(p, 3)); %x-Komponenten
12    d_phi0(p, 2) = d_phi0(p-1, 2) + d*cos(P(p, 3)); %y-Komponenten
13end
14
15%Ableitungen nach den Krümmungen c_i
16d_c_x = zeros(num_points, num_points); %x-Komponenten
17d_c_y = zeros(num_points, num_points); %y-Komponenten
18for p=3:num_points
19    for c=2:num_points-1
20        if p>c     
21%             d = distance(P(p-1, 1),P(p-1, 2),P(p, 1),P(p, 2));
22            d_c_x(p, c) = d_c_x(p-1, c) - d^2*sin(P(p, 3))/sqrt(1-d^2*r(c+1)^2/4);
23            d_c_y(p, c) = d_c_y(p-1, c) + d^2*cos(P(p, 3))/sqrt(1-d^2*r(c+1)^2/4);
24        end        
25    end   
26end
27
28
29%Messmatrix zusammensetzen
30H = zeros(2*numel(lambda), numel(r));
31count = 1;
32for i=1:numel(ind) %alle Messpunkteiterieren
33    H(count, 1)   = 0;   %Ableitung nach y0
34    H(count+1, 1) = 1;   
35    
36    H(count, 2)   = d_phi0(ind(i), 1);   %Ableitung nach phi0
37    H(count+1, 2) = d_phi0(ind(i), 2);   
38    
39    for c=3:ind(i) %Ableitung nach Krümmungen c
40%         d = distance(P(ind(i)-1, 1),P(ind(i)-1, 2),P(ind(i), 1),P(ind(i), 2));
41        if c==ind(i)
42            H(count, c)   = d_c_x(ind(i)-1, c-1) - lambda(i)*d^2*sin(P(ind(i), 3))/sqrt(1-d^2*r(c-1)^2/4);
43            H(count+1, c) = d_c_y(ind(i)-1, c-1) + lambda(i)*d^2*cos(P(ind(i), 3))/sqrt(1-d^2*r(c-1)^2/4);
44        else
45            H(count, c)   = d_c_x(ind(i), c-1);
46            H(count+1, c) = d_c_y(ind(i), c-1);
47        end        
48    end
49    
50    count = count + 2;
51end
52
53end
54
